- HEAD is not explicitly implemented, but since there is a GET route for the same path, the framework (Gin) will generally support HEAD requests by delegating to the GET handler. Therefore, HEAD is treated as acceptable here.
- Other methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE) are not defined for this endpoint in the provided code, so they are not acceptable.
